,Recommended,217200,18280436,"Posted: 1 October, 2015",all,♠-_Voltaire_-♠,"Normally, in my years of browsing Steam games on their store, I would look at this game, see the graphics and the price, and move on (NOOOO I dont judge games by graphics, and a lot of games that have these graphics now adays are worth playing, but not worth the price tag this one has, mind you).  But, if you pay attention to the reviews, there is a reason for the price.This game holds its weight even after over 15 years.  Extremely fun, very challenging, and a lot of fun to play turn by turn with your spose, children, siblings, friends, be it on LAN or on the same screen together taking turns.This game rivals Chess in its strategy, having so many different variables to use to conquer your opponent, and so many different ways to go about doing so.  The campaign is fun and all, in my opinion, by my greatest pleasure has been playing with friends and family, and in my own time, playing progessive deathmatch against the PC.  Each game you win it gets harder and harder with the odds more against you.Not to mention full custom course creation, as well as team creation.  Name 8 team members and choose the team flag, their accent/voice, and their grave stones for when the lil' guys die for you, even choose the victory song that plays at the end of a match.  Go even further and choose the amount of ammo you start with, what guns you start with, the time for each turn, round, match, falling damage on/off, mine timer duration, crate drop occurence, power of each weapon (nothing better than having a bow and arrow cause more damage than a **HOLY HAND GRENADE** but seriously, this game gives very little limitation to creating the perfect match for you and your friends.2 people left on map in a stalemate, afraid to move.  Sudden Death kicks in, it becomes a race to the top.  10/106 people left on map, a box drops from the sky.  Super banana bomb, it becomes a slaughter!!  10/104 people left on map, you throw a grenade that bounces back on you, and kills your last two guys.  10/10Don't bother yourself with the newer ""3D"" versions of this game. While fun, they are mere attempts at capturing the greatness that this game wasBuy this game!!!"
