,Recommended,217200,3948032,"Posted: 30 March, 2013",all,```skunk3```,"(Hours logged in-game only apply to the Steam version of W:A I purchased. The actual amount of time I've spent playing this game is incalculable.)Best game ever made, hands down.Better than all of the newer Worms titles. (Although we shall see if W.M.D. ends up being any good.) Unbeatable replay value and deeply strategic gaming. This game literally never gets old.I've been playing it online since 1999 and I'll be playing it until I die, probably.Looks are deceiving - what appears to be a simplistic, cartoony game for kids is actually the best online multi-player turn-based strategy game there is. The learning curve is practically endless. No matter how much you've played, you can always improve.This is also a fantastic choice for less hardcore Worms players if you merely want to have some 6-player action with your friends and laugh your heads off.I really don't understand why this game isn't more popular. To this day I have yet to find any game with as much replay value due to how customizable it is, and community-created schemes and maps are abundant.One word of warning to newbies: People have been playing this game for a LONG time. If you find yourself losing (and you will), don't be put off by it. Every match is a learning experience and this game takes time to master. Nobody becomes good at this overnight. The community in general is friendly and willing to answer questions.This game is digital crack cocaine. Yes, the graphics are dated, but the gameplay is outstanding."
