,Recommended,217200,16667446,"Posted: 23 June, 2015",all,SlyCooperFan1,"I distinctly remember playing (and loving) a game on Nickelodeon's website a long time ago called ""This Means War"", which was an artillery game based off of the show Catscratch. It was the only artillery game I had ever played for a long time, so I had no idea that there was a whole genre of it. A friend of mine introduced me to Worms Armageddon, and I have to say, I love it.The best part about Worms is the worms; they have cute animations, they react in hilarious ways to everything, and they feel like their own characters (especially once you put names to them). The gameplay is also fairly solid; there's no randomness, it's all down to strategy and skill. The multiplayer is relatively active for such an old game, but it's definitely best played with friends.Unfortunately, the game does show its age. The UI can be clunky, and the menu resolution (not the in-game resolution, which is fine) stays very low no matter what. If further patches could be made to revamp the UI, or at least remaster it for higher resolutions, it would be spectacular.Worms Armageddon is a classic in the Worms series as well as the artillery genre in general. For anyone looking for a hilarious time, I definitely recommend it."
