,Recommended,217200,9321379,"Posted: 2 March, 2014",all,R7038,"Ohhh Worms Armageddon, you NEED to play this game. Worms is a series that has been going on since the late 90's and this is actually just the third game in the series. Worms is a game where you control (duh) worms and they blow other worms up. The game is turn based and very strategic for how you want to use your turn. With Jet Packs, Ninja Ropes, and Parachutes for traversing terrain, You could go all the way out of your way to kill someone humiliatingly with the prod. Speaking of weapons, this game has a wide variety of weapons. Basic bazookas, grenades, air strikes, etc and then strange weapons like sheep, holy hand grenade, cows and other farm animals fill this game with very diverse weaponising.One of the best parts of Worms Armageddon specifically is the jump from the original and Worms 2 in balance via weapons. My favorite part of Worms Armageddon is the maps, though. Isn't it fun to blow through rubble, detritus and other worms on your way to victory? I think it is. Worms Armageddon has a relative amount of player customization with being able to change custom things such as maps, fanfare, voices (australian, cad, english, Soul Man), gravestones, flags, and worm profile names.Worms Armageddon has a feature of CPU opponents. The CPU's have a AI skill ranging from 1-5. On five, the AI will hit ridiculous wind-targeted rockets and grenades you couldn't have thought as possible. Level 1 CPU's tend to miss and blow themselves in to the water on occasion. If you use a fair weapon variety (my favorite is bazooka, air strike, grenade, shotgun) AI can be a formidable opponent. Oh yeah, SPEAKING of picking what weapons to use, that's another feature called game schemes. If you want to play with banana bombs, holy-hand grenades and armageddons only, then do it. Game schemes are very helpful.This game also has a single player mode, which is training, playing deathmatch vs. computer (VERY HARD AFTER A WHILE) doing missions (Eliminating 18 level 5 CPU's with one worm) and quick, simple games vs cpu. The single player mode is for unlocking small things for the game, such as indestructible terrain, a cheat that makes worms bleed when attacked, and more!For a game from 1999, it may be surprising to find out that it has an online multiplayer mode. If you jump into the land of WormNET, you will find different perspectives of worms armageddon such as Shopper, use ninja ropes and stuff to get crates with weapons, WxW, and Quickdraw. Worms Armageddon is vast worm world. Definitely one of my favorite games of all time."
