,Not Recommended,217200,19836316,"Posted: 21 December, 2015",all,Chris Cross Applesauce,"Trying to re-learn how to play this game has been one of the most aggrivating, and unrewarding experiences I've EVER had in gaming.Sure, everyone remembers Worms. You take turns angling and firing all kinds of different weapons in deathmatches, but I didn't remember all of the controls.The options menu has no way to change, or view the controls, nor does the basic training. The basic training is just a series of missions where it tells you to do something, but doesn't give you ANY inkling of how. I haven't played this game in over a decade, I don't remember how to open up the weapons menu. But if you don't figure it out in time, you fail the basic training mission, and have to go back not to the start of the mission, but three missions back. I can't even fathom what absolute moronic ""game designer"" thought that was a good idea. If you do two missions, and fail the third because of an unfair time limit, zero explaination of the controls, and zero guidance on how to use them.Seriously, I'm dropped into a BASIC TRAINING mission, where I need to reach a crate, and two targets on platforms slightly above me. It explains that I can use an uppercut to reach them. But if you use said uppercut, it's not nearly high enough to reach, and you've used up your single punch you get for that mission and fail. Now you need to complete the two previous missions to get back to this point and figure out what you did wrong. How am I supposed to figure out that not only do you need to jump, but you need to DOUBLETAP backspace (Which isn't even the jump key), and then hit space to double backflip, and then at the peak of your jump, use the uppercut? On top of that, the training missions are MANDATORY in order to play the real missions, and I STILL don't know how to open the weapons menu.So I'm sitting here, having only played for less than thirty minutes, and I'm frantically searching the internet on how I do absolute basic, and mandatory things like jumping, and opening the weapons menu.It's tragic, I have so many fond memories of this game, but back in the day, my friend introduced it to me and told me all the controls. Trying to learn the basic controls of this game is the biggest ""F-You"" I've EVER seen in gaming in my entire life.Buy this game for the nostalgia, but new players, stay the HELL away."
